-- 1. Dikoloti Festival 2026 – Senyetse (Se a tserema) vs Zambia Choir (Mochine)
INSERT INTO events (title, description, story, event_date, event_time, location, image_url) VALUES (
  'Senyetse Choir (Se a tserema) vs Zambia Choir (Mochine) – Dikoloti Festival 2026',
  'New Year''s Day 2026: Senyetse and Zambia Choir (Mochine) faced off at the Dikoloti Cultural Festival in Tshweneyagae.',
  'What better way to welcome the new year than with the thunder of traditional choirs? On 1 January 2026, Senyetse Choir—known as "Se a tserema"—met Zambia Choir, also known as "Mochine", at the Dikoloti Cultural Festival in Tshweneyagae. The stage was set for a memorable clash of voices, rhythms, and cultural pride.

The Dikoloti Festival, held in Tshweneyagae along the historic A2 highway between Lobatse and Kanye, draws choirs and performers from across the Southern District and beyond. This year was no ordinary year—Senyetse and Mochine brought their best, and the crowd knew it. From the moment we stepped onto the stage in traditional attire, the energy was electric. Our Setswana folksongs rang out; Mochine answered with their own repertoire. Back and forth we went—song for song, dance for dance—as elders ululated and children clapped along.

By the end of the day, there was no single winner. The real victory was shared: two choirs, two traditions, one celebration of heritage. Senyetse left Tshweneyagae with new friends, new inspiration, and a renewed commitment to preserving Setswana culture through song and dance. Se a tserema!',
  '2026-01-01',
  NULL,
  'Tshweneyagae, Southern District, Botswana',
  '/events/dikoloti-festival-2026/609152677_122257341974177133_5843049225200956723_n.jpeg'
);

-- 2. Dikoloti Festival 2025 – Senyetse vs Vultures Choir at Tshweneyagae
INSERT INTO events (title, description, story, event_date, event_time, location, image_url) VALUES (
  'Senyetse Choir vs Vultures Choir – Dikoloti Festival 2025 at Tshweneyagae',
  'January 2025: Senyetse Choir and Vultures Choir took to the stage at the Dikoloti Cultural Festival in Tshweneyagae.',
  'In January 2025, the Dikoloti Cultural Festival in Tshweneyagae witnessed a showdown between two powerhouse choirs: Senyetse Choir and Vultures Choir. The festival grounds buzzed with anticipation as crowds gathered under the Botswana sun, eager to see who would bring the most fire to the stage.

Senyetse opened with classic Setswana folksongs—songs of family, respect, and the land. The audience responded with ululations and applause. Then Vultures Choir took their turn, and the energy only grew. Back and forth we went—each choir raising the bar, each song drawing more people to their feet. Children sat at the front, wide-eyed; elders nodded in recognition of melodies passed down through generations.

The festival is not about winning or losing. It is about community, heritage, and the power of song to unite us. That day in Tshweneyagae, Senyetse and Vultures Choir showed what it means to celebrate culture together. We left with full hearts, new connections, and a deeper respect for the choirs that keep our traditions alive. Ke a leboga, Vultures Choir—until we meet again at Dikoloti.',
  '2025-01-02',
  NULL,
  'Tshweneyagae, Southern District, Botswana',
  '/events/dikoloti-festival-2025/476799785_122197821500177133_8848263504957386670_n.jpeg'
);

-- 3. Atang Amgano Wedding – Senyetse Choir member getting married
INSERT INTO events (title, description, story, event_date, event_time, location, image_url) VALUES (
  'Senyetse Choir Member Gets Married – Atang Amgano''s Wedding in Kanye',
  'One of our own said "I do" in Kanye. Senyetse Choir celebrated at Atang Amgano''s traditional Setswana wedding.',
  'When a Senyetse Choir member gets married, the whole choir shows up. In January 2025, our very own Atang Amgano tied the knot in Kanye, and we were there—not as performers only, but as family. The mood was joyous, the songs were familiar, and the day was one we will never forget.

Atang has been with Senyetse through countless rehearsals and performances. She knows our songs, our dances, our commitment to Setswana heritage. So when her wedding day arrived, we brought that same spirit to Kanye. Dressed in traditional attire, we sang songs of blessing—songs that honour marriage, family bonds, and the joy of two families becoming one. The patlo (engagement) had already been completed; the bogadi (bride-price) had been paid. This was the celebration.

Elders guided the proceedings. Families from both sides filled the space. And when Senyetse took the floor, people rose to dance. Some joined in; others watched with tears of joy. It was a reminder that our mandate extends beyond the stage: we participate in community life through folksongs, encouraging and presenting our cultural heritage in the moments that matter most. Atang Amgano, re a o lakaletsa—we wish you and your partner a lifetime of happiness. Pula!',
  '2025-01-15',
  NULL,
  'Kanye',
  '/events/atang-wedding/476300561_122196912368177133_992053082589293736_n.jpeg'
);

-- 4. Christmas 2024 – Senyetse vs Fanta Choir at Molapo-Wa-Basadi
INSERT INTO events (title, description, story, event_date, event_time, location, image_url) VALUES (
  'Senyetse Choir vs Fanta Choir – Christmas Showdown at Molapo-Wa-Basadi',
  '25 December 2024: Senyetse and Fanta Choir faced off in a festive clash at Molapo-Wa-Basadi.',
  'Christmas 2024 was not just another holiday concert. At Molapo-Wa-Basadi, Senyetse Choir and Fanta Choir went head-to-head in a celebration that blended festive spirit with fierce cultural pride. The stage was set, the crowds had gathered, and as the sun warmed the ground, the choirs took their turns.

Senyetse opened with traditional Setswana songs—songs of hope, gratitude, and community. We wore our finest; we sang with full hearts. Then Fanta Choir responded, and the energy in the air shifted. Back and forth we went—Senyetse with our heritage, Fanta with theirs—until the whole place was alive with music, dance, and joy. Children clapped; elders ululated. It was Christmas, and it was culture, and it was unforgettable.

By the end of the day, there were no losers. We had shared the stage, shared the moment, and reminded everyone present that choirs are not competitors alone—we are guardians of tradition, messengers of hope, and part of the same community. Senyetse left Molapo-Wa-Basadi with new friendships, full hearts, and a Christmas memory to last a lifetime. Pula e nnile!',
  '2024-12-25',
  NULL,
  'Molapo-Wa-Basadi',
  '/events/christmas-2024/477286013_122197822922177133_22826044634891392_n.jpeg'
);
